    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Maria Lydig Daly (1824 - 1894) was an American Democrat, Dirarist, and Unionist. Maria is the author of Diary of a Union Lady, 1861-1865, was active in the Democratic Party, the Women's Central Association for the Relief for the Army, the New York Botanical Garden, and many other collectives during the American Civil War. Daly was the daughter of Philip Mesier Lydig (1739 - 1872), the last landholder of the property that became the Bronx Park and the New York Botanical Garden, and Katherine Suydam, eldest daughter of John Suydam, an early settler of New Netherland, also known as a "Knickerbocker." Maria married jurist, lecturer, and writer Charles Patrick Daly (1816 - 1899), who was a member of the New York State Assembly, Chief Justice of the New York Court of Common Pleas, and president of the American Geographical Society. The Charles Patrick Daly Papers (1829-1897) are preserved at the New York Public Library, Archives and Manuscripts Division, in New York, NY. </field>
